{
  "stem": "19807.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 217.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, knowing all this, seeing the-- the-- and hearing that the Jews of [INAUDIBLE] and Macedonia were not spared and then all of a sudden, our lives were spared and then all of a sudden we're on a train going to Israel, we had to say with each other, you know what?",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were children.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Come on, we are 14-- I was 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But luckily, that trend could have been going in a different direction.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that's very--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --those are some of the feelings that we have with us while we're going to-- to Palestine, of course- jubilation and joy and-- and anticipation of a new life.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you can't divorce yourself and forget something which sheer miracle really had happened, that our lives were spared.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's said that the communists squelched it and there is no place on earth that 50,000 Jews were severed in their entirety during the Nazi occupation.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's no such thing and very few people know that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I hope to God that this tape will convey that to people and something will be done about it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, well, going to Israel on the train was-- was a real experience.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, away from the parents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I tell you, we were not overcome with sadness.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Don't forget we were kind of tough already by then.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had lived under the Nazis, we living under the most adverse conditions.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We've seen it all-- well, not all but we've seen a lot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So going to-- to-- to Palestine and looking forward to become part of a-- of a community there and a vital part of that community was exciting.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew what was expected there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
